  <div class="col-md-4"> <img src="sport1.jpeg" height="210" width="370"> <br>
  <small><h5>Bauchi Governor’s Wife Empowers 500 Women In Alkaleri LGA</h5>
The Wife of the Bauchi State Governor, Dr Aisha Mohammed, on Monday distributed various empowerment items  to no fewer than  500 women in Alkaleri Local  Government Area of the state.
News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that some of the items distributed, to make the beneficiaries self -reliant, includes sewing machines, knitting machines as well as cash to start-up their businesses.

NAN reports that the intervention , which was held at Alkaleri council secretariat, was made  under Al-Muhibbah Foundation , the pet project of Mohammed.

Speaking at the occasion, Mohammed  said that women were vulnerable members of the society who should be empowered, hence the need for such intervention.</small>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4"><img src="sport2.jpeg" height="210" width="370"> 
      <small><h5>Breaking: Supreme Court upholds Bala Mohammed’s election as Bauchi Governor</h5> 
The Supreme Court, on Monday, validated the election of Governor Bala Muhammed of Bauchi State.
A seven-man panel of the apex court led by Justice Sylvester Ngwuta unanimously dismissed the appeal filed by the All Progressives Congress and its governorship candidate, Muhammed Abubakar.

Justice Dattijo Muhammad, who read the lead judgment, held that the evidence of the appellants’ witnesses at the election tribunal was inadmissible.

He added that the appellants failed to demonstrate the perversity in the concurrent judgments of both the election tribunal and the Court of Appeal, which had both affirmed the victory of Bala and his party, the Peoples Democratic Party, to warrant the verdicts of the lower courts to be set aside.</small>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4"><img src="sport1.jpeg" height="210" width="370">
      <small><h5>NUBASS President Calls on FG to Immortalise Abubakar Tafawa Balewa</h5>

The National Union of Bauchi State Students (NUBASS) under the leadership of Amb. Kaloma March Yesterday 15/Jan on the streets of Bauchi to the Tomb of Sir. Abubakar Tafawa for the Remembrance of Nigeria First Prime Minister, a proud Legend of the State.


The student were seen carrying placards with different inscription calling Sir. Abubakar Tafawa a Legend for all and He deserve to be immortalized, upon an interview with the press the NUBASS President calls upon the Federal Government to Declare 15th January a public Holiday because of the indelible legacies of the legend!


Amb. Kaloma also calls upon the stakeholders of Bauchi State, Northeast and Nigeria at Large to help the Educational sector under the Scheme they initiated; Sir. Abubakar Tafawa Balewa Memorial Students Educational Trust Fund(ATBMSETF). So as to Help those from less privileged families and vulnerable children to achieve there dream of Education.</small>
